Entries.default: He averts his gaze.
"Always the Mataru are on edge of late. Restless as squalls."
"Amira's winds whip today."
"The Narrows? Ekera, I never seek trouble."
He hacks a blackish glob of phlegm onto the ground.
"Ondra be with you."
"A Watcher? In the Gullet?"
She blows her nose on the hem of her shirt.
She sniffles and coughs.
"Ondra's blessings."
Her stomach rumbles loudly.
His belly gurgles.
"What I wouldn't give for a bowl of fresh koÄ«ki."
He exhales a heavy cloud of whiteleaf.
"You never saw me here. And I never saw you."
"If the Mataru knew I come here, I will be lashed, ekera."
"I heard they serve bloatbelly eels here."
"That banded mitten crab smells all sorts of good."
"Yes, poor Roparu. But who pities the Unworthy? No one."
"Bottom's up, always. Till the copper's gone."
"Hungry and tired. Tired and hungry. Always."
His collarbone juts sharply as if whittled from his chest.
"Hylea save me, but I am hungry."
"Surely this hunger could rival Ondra's depths."
"I used to dream of food. Now I eat it."
Her fingers are thin, barely more than bones.
"Hear that? My belly's never quiet. But it's quiet lately."
"My belly's full with good food now."
This man's face seems fuller lately.
She looks less gaunt than she did before.
"Bless the Dawnstars. You'll find none kinder."
"They say we got pirates to thank for the food spoils. Or un-spoils, anyway."
"The Crown heard our cries. Now, the Mataru bring all sorts for feasting."
"Never has our share been larger. Our royals care for all within the tribe."
